					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I <em>think</em> colinvella is asking whether it would be a nice augment (the same as the &quot;allow more than 8 sprites per scanline&quot;) to treat slightly-negative Y scroll values as off-the-top.<br /><br />To which I basically have three thoughts:<br /><br />1- Games probably don't actually comply with that definition, but you won't know if you don't try it<br />2- It should really only be thought as applicable to PAL consoles anyway, since NTSC <em>televisions</em> already treat small positive values as off-the-top.<br />3- There should definitely be a toggle for &quot;authentic&quot; behavior instead of &quot;better than reality&quot; behavior.</div>

